<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2005-06-07b.39.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="39"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200506/ldhansrd/vo050607/text/50607-24.htm#50607-24_head0">
	Ethiopia: Humanitarian Assistance
</minor-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2005-06-07b.39.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100013" speakername="Baroness Amos" colon=":" colnum="39"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200506/ldhansrd/vo050607/text/50607-24.htm#50607-24_spmin0">
	<p pid="b.39.1/1">My right honourable friend the Secretary of State for International Development (Mr Hilary Benn) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p>
	<p pid="b.39.1/2">In response to the revised humanitarian appeal launched by the government of Ethiopia on <phrase class="date" code="2005-05-04">4 May 2005</phrase>, the Department for International Development (DfID) will make a contribution of &pound;5 million to assist the poor in life-threatening situations. This is in addition to &pound;1 million contributed through UNICEF in response to the initial December 2004 appeal.</p>
	<p pid="b.39.1/3">This is also in addition to the UK's commitment to provide &pound;70 million over the next three years to Ethiopia's Productive Safety Nets Programme, designed to provide predictable support for the estimated 5 million people in regular need of emergency assistance, and to tackle the underlying problems of food insecurity in Ethiopia.</p>
</speech>
